        "text": "Fornari's explanation can also be classified in the tradition of Melanie Klein. His thesis is that war is caused by the \"paranoid elaboration of grief\". Its function is to heal the paranoid and depressive fears that are inherent in every human being. War is like an iceberg, the smaller part of which can be observed on the surface, while the larger part remains hidden. On the surface, it serves as a defense against external dangers, while unconsciously it serves as a defense and security maneuver against terrifying fantasy entities (terrifiers) that are not flesh and blood and represent an absolute danger (as in nightmares)."
